A steel company, ABC steel, manufactures nuts and bolts. When x nuts are
produced, they can be sold for

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle{}-3x+500
\end{align*}

dollars each. When y bolts are produced, they can be sold for

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle{}-y+300
\end{align*}

dollars each.

Assume that nuts and bolts weigh 0.5kg each. How many nuts and how many
bolts must be produced to maximize the revenue from 100kg of steel?
Justify your answer.
